  <titleInfo>
    <title>[Letter] 1803 Feb. 1 [to] John McKnitt Alexander, Mecklenburg County, North Carolina / Peggy A. Ramsey</title>
  </titleInfo>
  <abstract>This is a letter from Peggy A. Ramsey dated February 1, 1803. The letter is to her grandfather, John McKnitt Alexander. Peggy writes about studying the Bible and letter writing. She reports having finished her shorter catechism. She also mentions that her family has suffered from the whooping cough.</abstract>
